“Commercial Use” means any use of the Software or a Modified Version that directly or indirectly supports, enables, promotes, or contributes to revenue, compensation, business activity, monetization, or commercial advantage.

“Modified Version” means any version, adaptation, translation, fork, refactor, extension, rewrite, integration, derivative work, or other project that is based on, copied from, adapted from, or substantially derived from the Software.

“Source Available” means that the complete, human-readable source code of the Software or Modified Version is publicly available under this same license.

“Network Use” means making the Software or a Modified Version available to others through a website, mobile app, web app, API, cloud service, hosted service, multiplayer service, online lobby system, or any other network-accessible system.

